/decl/cultural_info/culture/human_2020/ceres
	name = "Ceres"
	description = "You are from Ceres. the separation of Inner Space and Outer Space. economy of most colonys thrives on the booming industries of Asteroid Mining, Spaceship Manufacturing, and the Colonization of the Asteroid Belt. \
	With Ceres serving as a central hub for interplanetary trade and transportation to Outer and Inner Space, Ceres wields significant influence in shaping the future of space exploration and settlement. \
	However, the colonys also faces challenges inherent to its extraterrestrial environment, including the development of sustainable ecosystems, protection against cosmic radiation, and the equitable distribution of resources among its diverse population."
	economic_power = 0.7

/decl/cultural_info/culture/human_2020/belter
	name = "Belter"
	description = "You are from the Inner Belt These colonies, established by a combination of government initiatives and private enterprises, are pioneering of space exploration and resource exploitation. \
	With the United States, Soviet Union and private mining companies leading the way, the Inner Belt colonies thrive on the extraction of valuable resources such as water ice, iron, and rare metals from asteroids. \
	Despite the challenges of isolation, limited resources, and harsh environmental conditions, the inhabitants of these colonies are driven by the promise of wealth, scientific discovery, and the opportunity to establish a new human presence beyond the confines of Earth."
	economic_power = 0.7

/decl/cultural_info/culture/human_2020/spacer
	name = "Spacer"
	description = "You are from some station of the Inner Solar System life is a tapestry woven with threads of corporate enterprise, military presence, and scientific inquiry. These stations \
	owned primarily by multinational corporations, with some operated by the American military and Soviet Union, serve diverse purposes ranging from commercial trade hubs to research outposts and military installations. \
	Amidst the vast expanse of space, these stations are bustling centers of activity, facilitating interplanetary commerce, technological innovation, and strategic defense initiatives. \
	While the corporate-owned stations prioritize profit and resource extraction, military stations maintain vigilance against potential threats, and research stations push the boundaries of scientific knowledge in fields such as astrophysics, biology, and materials science."
	economic_power = 0.7
